403
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:41,480
you wouldn’t be here today.

404
00:27:43,420 --> 00:27:44,920
The play I wrote

405
00:27:46,420 --> 00:27:48,840
is also about a woman.

406
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:51,320
I have heard a lot of stories about women.

407
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:55,080
What kind of woman did you write?

408
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,480
This woman

409
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:01,960
eloped with the man she loves

410
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:03,600
and ran away from home.

411
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:05,760
Ms. Li.

412
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:06,720
Then

413
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:07,760
this man

414
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:09,800
went out to do business

415
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:13,080
and never come back.

416
00:28:13,420 --> 00:28:14,840
So this woman

417
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,920
stayed in her home alone.

418
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,480
It’s kind of like…

419
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:21,840
That… That…

420
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:22,920
Qin Luofu.

421
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,680
And then,

422
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:28,640
she got a lot of lovers.

423
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,680
But her lovers came

424
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:32,600
and left.

425
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:34,160
And new lovers came.

426
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,680
And then,

427
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:40,680
the woman figured it out.

428
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:43,040
She thought that the love

429
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,560
of her lovers

430
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:46,920
is just like the clouds.

431
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:47,680
It’s…

432
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:48,600
It’s all unreliable.

433
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:52,040
Only herself can control her fate

434
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:53,520
and get happiness.

435
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,280
It starts to be interesting.

436
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:57,440
It starts to be interesting.

437
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:59,400
Then how…

438
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:02,480
How did she grasp her happiness?

439
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:06,440
She opened her own weaving workshop

440
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:09,440
and took in many widows and orphan girls.

441
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:12,520
And then paid all her attention

442
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:13,720
on weaving.

443
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:16,040
Then the weaving she made was really beautiful.

444
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:19,160
Even the robe of the Queen was made by her.

445
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,960
They asked her to make it.

446
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:24,200
Isn’t that…

447
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,440
That…

448
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:28,080
Royal Clothes?

449
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,440
I see.

450
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:31,440
I see.

451
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:37,080
You are saying that

452
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:39,320
women should

453
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:41,480
grasp their own fate.

454
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,560
They should become rich.

455
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,800
It’s OK if you want to

456
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,440
